<!DOCTYPE task
  PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/dtd/task.dtd">
<task id="convert-XML-to-JSON">
  <title>XML to JSON Converter</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Convert XML to JSON</indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML to JSON tool</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes a useful and simple tool for converting XML files to JSON.
        It can be found in the <uicontrol product="developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
          product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu.</p>
      <p>To convert an XML document to JSON, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="procedure-import-from-HTML">
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <uicontrol>XML to JSON</uicontrol> action from the <uicontrol
            product="developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu.</cmd>
        <stepresult><ph>The <uicontrol>XML to JSON</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed:</ph><p>
            <fig>
              <title>XML to JSON Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/convert-xml-to-json-dialog.png" id="image_twc_5qf_jd"/>
            </fig>
          </p></stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Choose or enter the <uicontrol>Input URL</uicontrol> of the XML document.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Choose the path of the <uicontrol>Output file</uicontrol> that will contain the
          conversion JSON result.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Check the <uicontrol>Open in Editor</uicontrol> option to open the JSON result of the
          conversion in the <ph keyref="product"/> JSON Editor.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Convert</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <result>
      <p>The original XML document is now converted to a JSON document.<fig>
          <title>Example: XML to JSON Operation Result</title>
          <image href="../img/convert-xml-to-json.png" id="image_pgg_nkf_jd"/>
        </fig></p>
    </result>
  </taskbody>
</task>